author: timesunion.com
title: Rodger's Quick Take
text: The Mets keep rolling out their stable of young arms, one after another against the Dodgers. Steven Matz takes the ball on Tuesday night in Game 4, which means Jacob deGrom will go on regular rest if they need him in a deciding Game 5. The Mets have four stud pitchers and all of them can be dominant. Matz, 24, was 4-0 with a 2.27 ERA in six starts. You do worry about the stiffness he has been battling in his back. But Matz tells manager Terry Collins he feels fine, and his rehab start in Port St. Lucie last week went well. All systems are a go for Matz to make his postseason debut.
